From: NeilBrown <neilb@suse.com>
Subject: fix detection of race between fcntl-setlk and close.
Git-commit: 7f3697e24dc3820b10f445a4a7d914fc356012d1
References: bsc#1140965
Patch-mainline: v4.5-rc1

A recent backport broke detction of races between setlk (in one thread)
and close (in another).
Restore the correct upstream code.

Signed-off-by: NeilBrown <neilb@suse.com>

---
 fs/locks.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/fs/locks.c
+++ b/fs/locks.c
@@ -1872,7 +1872,7 @@ int fcntl_setlk(unsigned int fd, struct
 		f = fcheck(fd);
 		spin_unlock(&current->files->file_lock);
 		if (f != filp) {
-			flock.l_type = F_UNLCK;
+			file_lock->fl_type = F_UNLCK;
 			error = do_lock_file_wait(filp, cmd, file_lock);
 			WARN_ON_ONCE(error);
 			error = -EBADF;
